text: This charming 2-bedroom, 2-bath home is located on over 6 and a half useable acres, offering a perfect blend of country living and convenience. The property features an area for horses in front of the home, along with a 2-stall stable, feed barn, and corral just across the driveway. The home itself is complemented by an attached carport on the back side, a fenced front yard shaded by trees, and a cozy covered patio ideal for outdoor relaxation. For hobbyists or anyone needing extra space, a huge garage/workshop is available with easy access. Additionally, the back part of the property offers four covered parking areas-perfect for trailers, extra vehicles, or whatever else you may need to store. With ample useable land and the potential for a variety of outdoor activities, this home is a true horse lover's dream. Best of all, it's still less than 30 minutes from town, combining the tranquility of rural living with easy access to city amenities. This is a rare opportunity to own a fantastic horse property!

5.74 acre ranchette horse property in Aravaipa, with private access to miles of BLM and state land. Complete equestrian training set up, with LED-lit team roping area, barns, multiple fenced/shaded paddocks, and enough storage for 1.5+ semi-loads of hay. This meticously maintained property is completed fenced and gated, with video survelliance for security. Generac propane generator along with a private well allow you to continue living normally during a power outage, with the potential for offgrid living. The impressive block home features a 50 year rated metal roof, new Renewal by Anderson windows, recently installed dual unit HVAC system, and premium finishes: granite countertops, stainless appliances, custom knotty alder soft close cabinetry, custom rock fireplace, and tile flooring throughout. Primary bathroom features soaking tub and separate shower, with intricate tile surrounds. Huge primary walk-in closet with custom shelving and two wall safes. The off-kitchen laundry room features additional storage cabinets, an upright freezer, and large sink. Relax in the covered outdoor kitchen area, with sink and grill. The expansive acreage features 9 carport bays, drip irrigation/ 20+ hose bibs for watering, a private workshop with wood-burning stove, along with multiple outbuildings and a tremendous amount of storage. The productive private well has a 1500 gallon tank with recently replaced booster and well pumps. Home features Ecowater softener/filtration system, along with RO at sink for drinking water. Stone and block main entrance features designer custom gates, and home is surrounded by travertine walkways/patios. Corrals use schedule 40 and schedule 80 piping, along with welded wire fencing. Enjoy rural living and incredible mountain views, only 40 minutes from Oro Valley. No HOA! Property uses a Winkelman/Dudleyville zip code, but is located in the Aravaipa canyon area.

Experience the Magic of Aravaipa Canyon, a Private 47-Acre Nature Retreat. Welcome to Aravaipa Farms, a truly extraordinary 47-acre sanctuary nestled in the heart of the spectacular Aravaipa Canyon. Surrounded by untouched wilderness, dramatic canyon walls, and the soothing sounds of a rare, perennial creek, this is a place where nature takes center stage and peace becomes a way of life. Designed for those who crave space, solitude, and sustainability, the main residence is a beautiful 3-bedroom, 3-bath straw bale home that blends rustic charm with modern comfort. Rich natural materials, thick adobe-colored walls, and thoughtful design create a warm, grounded living environment that stays cool in the summer and cozy in the winter. In addition to the main home, a classic 3 bedroom, 2-bath farmhouse and several charming guest casitas provide comfortable space for visiting friends and familyor simply room to spread out and enjoy life at your own pace. The land itself is a natural wonder. Thirteen irrigated acres support a thriving orchard of more than 900 mature fruit treesapricots, peaches, pears, and moreoffering seasonal bounty and endless beauty. A sprawling 11,000-square-foot organic garden is perfect for those who dream of cultivating their own food or simply enjoying fresh, homegrown produce. With generous water rights, four reliable wells, and year-round flow from Aravaipa Creek, you'll never worry about water supply. Outdoor living is a daily joy here. Swim in the heated pool, gather around outdoor fireplaces, nap in the shade of a ramada, or simply take in the quiet canyon views from one of several peaceful patios. The night skies here are extraordinaryclear, dark, and filled with stars. Additional structures include a large workshop, chicken coop, and a recently built caretaker's home, all blending seamlessly into the landscape and supporting a low-impact, sustainable lifestyle. The land offers endless potential for gardening, hiking, horseback riding, or simply exploring the surrounding wilderness. Located just 1.5 hours from Tucson and 2 hours from Phoenix, this property offers a rare combination of privacy and accessibility. With the Aravaipa Canyon Wilderness Preserve next door, you'll enjoy one of Arizona's most protected and awe-inspiring natural areasideal for hiking, birdwatching, and reconnecting with nature. Aravaipa Farms is more than a propertyit's a place to breathe, to dream, and to live in harmony with the land. Come see what it feels like to truly get away. Envision your own "The Big Little Farm."
